    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The answer is already given. You can use your IDE like <code>IntelliJ</code> to provide the env variables, you can do that as the following</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pehWS.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pehWS.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/fjiKz.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/fjiKz.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/d5e9d.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/d5e9d.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
